    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Headlights
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Headlights</title>
        <table id="t0822208" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Headlights</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.48in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch off, disconnect conn. (1). Then turn headlight switch on and
                                place dimmer switch in high beam position, and at (1) measure voltage from circuit 52F
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1), 52F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch on and dimmer switch in low beam position. At (1) measure
                                voltage from circuit 53B to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1), 53B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch off at (1) measure resistance from circuit 52-GE to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(1), 52-GE to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Switch circuits check good. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 52-GE, 52-GF, or 11-GF to ground stud at
                                left dash panel, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Turn off headlight switch. Reconnect connector (1), and disconnect connector (296).
                                Turn headlight switch on and place dimmer switch in low beam position. Measure voltage
                                at (296) from circuit 53D to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(296), 53D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53B or 53D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch still on, place dimmer switch in high beam position. Measure
                                voltage at (296) from circuit 52D to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(296), 52D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52F or 52D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch still on and dimmer sw. in high beam position, measure voltage
                                at (296) from circuit 52D to 52-GE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(296), 52D to 52-GE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor conn. in circuit 52-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn off headlight switch. Reconnect conn. (296) and disconnect conn. (77). Turn on
                                headlight switch and place dimmer switch in low beam position. At (77) measure voltage
                                from yellow 2 wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(77), yellow 2 wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in yellow 2 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, place dimmer switch in high beam position. At (77) measure
                                voltage from yellow 1 wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(77), yellow 1 wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in yellow 1 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, and dimmer switch in high beam position, at (77) measure
                                voltage from yellow 1 wire to white 2 wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(77), yellow 1 wire to white 2 wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in white 2 or yellow 1 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn off headlight switch. Disconnect conn. (211). Turn on headlight switch and place
                                dimmer switch in low beam position. At (211) measure voltage from circuit 53C to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(211), 53C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, place dimmer switch in high beam position. At (211) measure
                                voltage from circuit 52E to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(211), 52E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, and dimmer switch in high beam position, at (211) measure
                                voltage from circuit 52E to 52-GA.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(211), 52E to 52-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor conn. in circuit 52-GA, or circuit 64-GC to cab ground J7, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn off headlight switch, and reconnect connector (211).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (71). Turn on headlight switch and place dimmer switch in low beam
                                position. At (71) measure voltage from yellow 2 wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(71), yellow 2 wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in yellow 2 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, place dimmer switch in high beam position. At (71) measure
                                voltage from yellow 1 wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(71), yellow 1 wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in yellow 1 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With headlight switch on, and dimmer switch in high beam position, at (71) measure
                                voltage from yellow 1 wire to white 2 wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(71), yellow 1 wire to white 2 wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in white 2 or yellow 1 wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Headlight circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
